data.name: page_size
data.prompt: The number of items to return for each page. Sending this parameter with the query will enable paging for the returned collection.

data.name: page_number
data.prompt: The number of the page to be returned. This requires that paging be turned on by also providing the page_size parameter.

queries.prompt: Given a user ID, returns members directly associated with the user as well as members associated with the user via a shared access contact.
BETA: (this query is subject to change or suddenly disappear) Given a a team_id or division_id, returns all members that are commissioners of the divisions that the team is in.

Given a user ID, returns all members associated with user's active season teams.  If include_archived_teams (boolean) parameter is supplied, members associated with archived teams will be returned as well.

commands.prompt: Given source_member_ids (array) and a destination_team_id, source members and related member data will be imported to the destination team. Newly created members will be returned.

data.name: send_invites
data.prompt: Whether or not to create and send invitations for each imported member. Valid values are either 'true' or 'false' and will default to 'false'

commands.prompt: BETA: (This endpoint subject to change) Searches the division and subdivision for the members meeting the search criteria.

data.name: division_id
data.prompt: Id of the division and descendants to search

data.name: is_unassigned
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that aren't assigned to a team. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_activated
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that have a user. Not used if blank.
